gal advice and legislative services to UK Government departments, and in particular advice on Scots law and the Scottish devolution settlement.  The team also assesses the impact of Scottish Government legislation going through the Scottish Parliament in support of the Advocate General’s statutory functions under section 33 of the Scotland Act 1998.</p>\n","role_payment_type":null},"document_type":"board_member_role","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2013-05-29T09:39:57Z","schema_name":"role","title":"Head of Advisory and Legislation Division","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2020-07-22T11:23:56Z","schema_name":"role_appointment","title":"Victoria MacDonald - Head of Advisory and Legislation Division","withdrawn":false}]},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2024-01-24T09:56:43Z","schema_name":"person","title":"Victoria MacDonald","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/people/victoria-macdonald","withdrawn":false},{"api_path":"/api/content/government/people/james-gaughan","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/people/james-gaughan","base_path":"/government/people/james-gaughan","content_id":"b437239a-a4b7-477f-ad20-12f411eecf53","details":{"image":null,"privy_counsellor":false},"document_type":"person","links":{"role_appointments":[{"content_id":"1fea3b0d-acbd-4e6b-bf34-618a8224bc19","details":{"current":true,"ended_on":null,"person_appointment_order":1,"started_on":"2024-02-01T00:00:00+00:00"},"document_type":"role_appointment","links":{"role":[{"content_id":"8461c3df-c0f1-11e4-8223-005056011aef","details":{"body":"<p>The Legal Secretary is responsible for supporting the Advocate General in his various roles, including in his capacity as one of the UK Government’s Law Officers, as a UK Government Minister, and as the UK Government’s representative in the House of Lords. The Legal Secretary also leads a legal team in the Legal Secretariat to the Advocate General, leads the Advocate General’s Private Office team, and u